# AI Virtual Try-On Application - Product Plan and Implementation Design

## 1. Product Overview

### 1.1 Product Vision
Create an engaging, vibrant AI-powered virtual try-on experience that allows users to upload their photos and see themselves in different clothing styles from a curated collection.

### 1.2 Core User Journey
```
Upload Photo -> Select Clothing -> AI Processing -> View Result -> Download/Share
```

---

## 2. Product Feature Modules

### 2.1 Photo Upload Module
**User Story**: As a user, I want to upload a photo of myself so that I can try on different clothes.

**Features**:
- Drag-and-drop upload area with visual feedback
- Click-to-browse file selector
- Image preview with zoom capability
- Image requirements guidance (full body, good lighting, etc.)
- Basic image validation (format, size, resolution)
- Option to retake/reupload

**Interaction Flow**:
1. User enters the app and sees an inviting upload area
2. User drags photo or clicks to select
3. Preview shows the uploaded image
4. User can adjust/crop if needed
5. Confirm to proceed to clothing selection

### 2.2 Clothing Library Module
**User Story**: As a user, I want to browse and select from a variety of clothing options.

**Features**:
- Categorized clothing gallery (Tops, Dresses, Pants, etc.)
- Filter by style (Casual, Formal, Sporty, etc.)
- Filter by color
- Clothing item cards with preview image
- Quick preview hover effects
- Selected item highlight

**Interaction Flow**:
1. User sees clothing categories as tabs or filters
2. User browses clothing items in a grid layout
3. Clicking an item shows details and selects it
4. Visual confirmation of selection
5. Proceed to AI processing

### 2.3 AI Processing Module
**User Story**: As a user, I want to see my photo transformed with the selected clothing.

**Features**:
- Animated processing indicator
- Progress feedback with stages
- Estimated time display
- Cancel option
- Error handling with retry

**Interaction Flow**:
1. User clicks "Try On" button
2. Loading animation appears
3. Progress stages shown (Analyzing, Processing, Generating)
4. Result appears when ready

### 2.4 Result Display Module
**User Story**: As a user, I want to see my virtual try-on result clearly and take action on it.

**Features**:
- Before/After comparison slider
- Full-screen view option
- Download button (original quality)
- Share options (social media, copy link)
- "Try Another" button
- Save to gallery (if user accounts implemented)

**Interaction Flow**:
1. Result displays with smooth transition
2. User can compare before/after
3. User downloads or shares
4. Option to try more clothes

---

